<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Level Limit Applications and Problems</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?The RealmWeaver">The RealmWeaver</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 12:34 p.m. 9/2/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Level Limit Applications and Problems<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR></STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>Level limits are probably one of the most promising topics being discussed/considered at the current time. However, the input I have gathered from posters on this forum and elsewhere leads me to believe that there is a problem inherent in imposing level limit restrictions in EverQuest. The headache of grouping calculations have been discussed already, and the problem raised by large groups where some players are "in range" while others are out, etc.

<P>I believe this problem originates from an unbalance in the power increase of in EverQuest's level system; in order to impose a system of level limits, it is almost a necessity to have a balanced power-gauge so each limit can be arithmetically derived instead of just using guesswork.
<P>In other words, if the levels were balanced as far as power is concerned, we could simply impose a +- 5 level limit, and impose it on the sum of group levels as well. In other words, a group of two level 10s could be challegend by a 15-25. A group of three level 10s could face a 25-35, etc. For this to work, however, the sum power of two level 10s must be rougly equal to a level 20. As far as I have heard and read, this is not the case. So we must be wary when imposing level limits of a static size on an unbalanced system. Will the fight between a level 50 and 45 be as evenly matched as between a 20 and 15, or 10 and 5? Will a group of 3 tens be subject to the wrath of a 30? If so, how will they fare?
<P>At any rate, what I am warning against is focusing too much on the numbers and not enough on the actual power of a player of that level. A balance must be reached before any restrictions can be effectively imposed.
<P>The RealmWeaver
<BR>dcc5500@rit.edu
<BR>ICQ: 30795819
<BR>IM: WrldWeaver
<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
